Workmen discover grenade in Coatbridge streetA NUMBER of houses in Burnbank Street, Coatbridge have been evacuated after a grenade was found by workmen.The road has been closed and drivers are been told to take alternative routes.A police spokeswoman said: “At around 1.10pm police received a report of a grenade being found by workmen in Burnbank Street, Coatbridge.“BOD is in attendance and as a precaution a number of properties have been evacuated.“Emergency services are still on the scene.”